Output:
  {{ANALYZER_NAME}}-analysis/output/runs/<run-id>/analysis.json
  {{ANALYZER_NAME}}-analysis/output/runs/<run-id>/coverage.json
  {{ANALYZER_NAME}}-analysis/overrides.json        (repo-level, shared across runs)
```

## Hard rules

- Decisions live in the closed set `[{{DECISION_ENUM_NO_NULL}}, null]`.
- Never skip validation. Every phase validates before the next begins.
- Never write redacted-key values in plaintext.
- Hard-fail on schema violations. Warnings go to `coverage.degradations[]`.
- Identity = `({{ID_FIELD}}, source.snippet_normalized_sha256)`. That pair
  is the contract between the agent and the override engine; any change to
  either invalidates replay.

## Notes for the author

`$SKILL_DIR` resolution is covered by the Variable model section at the
top. In a Claude Code session launched with `--add-dir` over the target
repo, pass the skill dir explicitly as an argument or hard-code the
path (`.claude/skills/analyze-{{ANALYZER_NAME}}`) depending on your
install.

Phase C.1 (ad-hoc + config) is optional per domain — if your analyzer
has no ad-hoc or config-driven candidates, that half is a no-op but
Phase C.2 (expected-entities backstop) still runs whenever the oracle
file exists.
